rary pedagogy. A theoretical part encompasses the theoretical principles of education science, learning theories, didactic principles, and models. The subsequent practical part includes introductory articles on didactic concepts and specific methods for education practice in libraries.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aBibliothek. 4aDidaktik. 4aLernen. 4aPädagogik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aLibrary.  aeducation.  alearning.  apedagogy.1 aBrandt, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuhlmann, Frauke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeeg, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEarnshaw, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEigenbrodt, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEndres, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelkenmeier, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelkenmeier, Ute, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFisseler, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrick, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFritz, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrye, Silke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeorgy, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGläser, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c